body_text.text:
Obesity is a common disturbance in donkeys in developing countries (Figs. 1
and 2
). This species is highly efficient in using low-quality feedstuff and has lower energy requirements than horses. When able to access to high-quality or calorie-rich feed, donkeys are prone to accumulate adipose tissue, even without overfeeding. In that sense, they can be considered easy keepers.
